HEADWORD: Acidifier
<hw>A*cid"i*fi`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A simple or compound principle, whose presence is necessary to
produce acidity, as oxygen, chlorine, bromine, iodine, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acidify</ent>⟦br⟧
